item.description:
Often we&rsquo;ll want to use Ansible to manage many servers, but some of those servers may not sit on the same area of the network. They might be in a Dematerialized Zone (DMZ) and only be accessible via a Bastion / Jumpbox server.
We can configure the Ansible Server to recognise Jumpbox configuration, so that it runs Ansible Playbooks on the DMZ Server, as though it were directly available;
Configuration  Firstly, make sure SSH keys are set up correctly.
